        "short_description": "A major backwater lake in Kerala known as the gateway to the state’s extensive backwater network.",
        "detailed": "Ashtamudi Lake is the second-largest and one of the most important wetlands in Kerala. The name ‘Ashtamudi’ means ‘eight coned’, referring to its eight arms or channels. Historically, Kollam was a bustling international port, and Ashtamudi Lake played a key role in waterway transport, trade, and cultural exchange. Today, it is a prominent tourism hub famous for serene boat cruises and houseboats."
